He said there is also no reason for citizens to stop working. "Work has to go on and that’s why even parliament is moving on with its schedule,” the Citizen newspaper quotes him as saying. President Magufuli recently said gatherings in churches and mosques had not been banned yet despite a coronavirus outbreak because that was where there was "true healing". The East African nation has closed all schools, colleges and universities and suspended all sporting events for at least 30 days after the country confirmed its first case on 16 March. The country has so far recorded 13 cases of coronavirus.
